rebel fighters captured tanks, armoured trucks and heavy artillery at the battle at gelebeda in northeastern tigray province on march 12, according to yemeni kedani, a spokesman for the tigre people's liberation front
however, his reports could not be independently confirmed. the ethiopian government rarely comments on rebel reports
kedani did not specify how many ethiopian army troops were killed in the gelebeda battle, nor did he say if there were casualties among the rebels
on march 7, kedani claimed the guerrillas killed more than 2,500 ethiopian soldiers and took control of three towns
kedani also charged that the ethiopian government was bombing civilian areas in tigray province. he said the bombing began immediately after ethiopian president mengistu haile mariam secretly visited the area in february
kedani's group is one of several in northern ethiopia fighting for independence from the addis ababa government
