they were angered over a tentative contract agreement reached by government and union negotiators on sunday
union leaders criticized monday's walkout, the latest strike in a dispute that has plagued air travelers since the fall. unlike this walkout, most of the strikes have been called in advance to give travelers a chance to find other transportation
foreign carriers reported delays of about 30 minutes monday
