a national police spokesman, yehoshua goldapfel, on sunday said that 450 of the 850 arab police in the occupied territories ``have asked to leave the force.'' he left open the possibility more would depart
the police control crime and direct traffic, but they are not used to quell arab rioting in the occupied lands, now in its fourth month
