a unit of wickes cos. inc. said monday it has formed a joint venture with shiroki corp. of yokohama, japan, to design and manufacture window regulators for the north american auto market
the wickes unit, wickes manufacturing co. of southfield, mich., and shiroki currently are leading suppliers of components to automakers in the united states and japan
window regulators control the speed and position of power windows, which wickes said are expected to dominate an increasingly large share of the u.s. market
wickes manufacturing makes a variety of electroninc and mechanical auto components and last fiscal year sold about $1 billion in original equipment to automakers. it also sells smaller amounts of auto parts in the secondary market
united artists communications inc. announced that is has formed corsair pictures, a new motion picture company based in new york
denver-based united artists, one of the nation's biggest movie operators with about 2,050 motion picture screens, said monday that corsair will develop a slate of quality films made with low and moderate budgets of $3 million to $10 million each
the new company, to be privately financed by united artists, will be headed by frank perry, a film producer and director. perry, who won an academy award nomination for best director for ``david and lisa,'' will be president and chief executive officer of corsair
perry said he envisions corsair producing three or four feature films in its first year, although that could vary depending on the number of quality projects and filmmakers available. ``corsair will be governed by quality and economic logic, not quantity,'' he said
last week, united artists and united cable television corp. agreed to combine their operations into a $3.8 billion concern that would rank as one of the nation's biggest cable tv companies
united artists has about 800,000 cable subscribers, while united cable has around 1.1 million
united artists also announced monday that its taurus entertainment co., a film marketing and distribution group, will report to perry in the future. perry will also oversee the company's recently acquired interest in ``think entertainment,'' a movie production company founded and run by actress-producer shelley duvall
perry's producing and directing credits include ``last summer,'' ``diary of a mad housewife,'' ``play it as it lays,'' ``rancho deluxe,'' ``mommie dearest,'' ``compromising positions'' and ``hello again.''
husky oil ltd. of canada is considering offering texaco inc. a cash infusion of at least $1 billion to help persuade texaco to sell husky a majority interest in texaco canada ltd., according to a published report
a texaco spokeswoman declined comment on the report carried in monday's editions of the wall street journal. officials at husky, based in calgary, alberta, did not return phone calls
the journal said robert blair, co-chairman of husky, said in an interview he remains very interested in acquiring the texaco unit and will step up his efforts in a trip to new york this week
blair added that husky would be willing to pay $2.4 billion to $2.7 billion for texaco's 78 percent interest in the toronto-based unit of texaco, the journal said
the estimated purchase price does not include the possible $1 billion cash infusion from husky, the journal said. it was not immediately clear what form a cash infusion might take
blair told the journal he hopes to present texaco a ``mutually attractive plan'' under which the two canadian companies would merge under husky's control. he added that texaco would have to sell enough of its interest to give husky a stake of at least 51 percent
blair said his recent phone messages have not been answered by james kinnear, texaco's chief executive
texaco is planning to sell about $3 billion in assets as part of its plan to emerge from chapter 11 protection by late next month
texaco filed for protection from creditors under chapter 11 of federal bankruptcy law last april to forestall enforcement of a $10.3 billion damages judgment for interfering with pennzoil co.'s acquisition of an interest in getty oil co. in 1984. texaco settled the dispute in december by agreeing to pay pennzoil $3 billion
